<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>Students who took Advanced Placement courses in high school and earned a score of 3 or higher on the exam may be eligible for college credit. Score reports need to be submitted directly from the College Board to the SFCC Records Office for placement determination.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.sfcc.edu/files/SFCCCatalog1011_pt1.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

